article.headline: North Dakota St. 87, Winston-Salem 63
article.story: WINSTON-SALEM, N.C. (AP) -- Ben Woodside and Brett Winkelman each scored a game-high 22 points to help North Dakota State defeat Winston-Salem 87-63 on Saturday. Andre Smith added 17 points and Mike Nelson finished with 16 points for the Bison (11-6), who shot a season-high 69.6 percent from the field. Winkelman pulled down a game-high nine rebounds. North Dakota St. had a 45-33 lead at the break before the Bison extended their lead to as many as 26 points with 2:13 remaining. The Bison hit 80 percent from beyond the arc and snapped a two-game winning streak for Winston-Salem (3-19). Winston-Salem hit 40 percent of its field goal attempts, went 31.3 percent on 3-pointers and finished 52.6 percent from the free throw line. Darius Floyd led Winston-Salem with 21 points, while Brian Fisher added 12 points and Jamal Durham scored 10.
